Package io.cyborgcode.roa.framework.parameters

Interface DataForge<T extends Enum<T>>

public interface DataForge<T extends Enum<T>>
Defines a contract for dynamically generating test data within the framework.

Implementations of this interface serve as structured data providers, ensuring consistent and reusable test data generation.

The data creation process is managed through a Late instance, allowing deferred initialization until the data is explicitly needed. Additionally, implementations provide an enumeration reference that identifies the specific data model.

  • Method Details

    • dataCreator

      Late<Object> dataCreator()
      Provides a deferred test data creation mechanism.

      Implementations return a Late instance that generates the test data object when required. This allows for on-demand data creation rather than instantiating all test data at the start.

      Returns:
      A Late instance responsible for creating test data objects.

    • enumImpl

      T enumImpl()
      Returns the enumeration instance associated with the test data model.

      This method ensures that test data can be uniquely identified and retrieved in a structured manner using its corresponding enum representation.

      Returns:
      An Enum instance representing the test data definition.
